18 neoconservatives wrote a letter to President Clinton urging him to aim above all at the removal

28:13.040 --> 28:19.120
of Saddam Hussein's regime from power. That now needs to become the aim of American foreign policy.

28:20.800 --> 28:25.280
Again, many, most in this case, of the signatories became officials in the Bush

28:25.280 --> 28:31.280
administration, including Elliot Abrams, Richard Armataj, John Bolton, Paula Dobriansky, Richard

28:31.280 --> 28:38.720
Perle, Donald Rumsfeld, and Paul Wolfowitz. In January of 2001, as George W. Bush was to be

28:38.720 --> 28:44.960
sworn in as the 43rd president, the Jerusalem Post's Washington correspondent, Janine Zakaria,

28:44.960 --> 28:50.480
reported on the emerging group of officials who will steer U.S.-Israel relations during the next

28:50.480 --> 28:56.560
four years. She declared Iraqi President Saddam Hussein is quietly developing weapons of mass

28:56.560 --> 29:01.680
destruction. Regarding Paul Wolfowitz's appointment as number two at the Pentagon,

29:02.320 --> 29:09.040
pro-Israel communities are jumping for joy. Wolfowitz is considered a strong supporter of Israel.

29:09.680 --> 29:14.000
He has been one of the loudest proponents of a tough policy toward Iraq,

29:14.000 --> 29:19.520
focused on finding a way to bring down Saddam Hussein's regime. Jumping for joy indeed,

29:19.520 --> 29:24.880
in fact, for his role in the Iraq invasion, the Jerusalem Post would name Wolfowitz Man of the

29:24.880 --> 29:32.560
Year. No question, this was Paul Wolfowitz's year. On September 15, 2001, at a meeting in Camp

29:32.560 --> 29:38.880
David, he advised President George W. Bush to skip Kabul and train American guns on Baghdad.

29:39.520 --> 29:45.040
In the process, Wolfowitz became the most influential U.S. Deputy Defense Secretary ever.

29:45.040 --> 29:50.720
Can you so much as name anyone else who held the post? The war in Iraq had many authors,

29:50.720 --> 29:56.240
Donald Rumsfeld, Dick Cheney, Tony Blair, George Bush. What's not in dispute is that

29:56.240 --> 30:02.400
Wolfowitz is the principal author of the Doctrine of Preemption, which framed the war in Iraq,

30:02.400 --> 30:07.600
and which, when it comes to it, will underpin U.S. action against other rogue states.

30:08.240 --> 30:14.080
Following September 11, many people grasped intuitively that it was useless to contain

30:14.080 --> 30:20.320
or deter foes for whom suicide was an acceptable option. The difference with Wolfowitz is that

30:20.320 --> 30:26.960
he's been talking about this since at least 1992. When President Bush says America will not permit

30:26.960 --> 30:31.600
the world's most dangerous regimes to threaten us with the world's most destructive weapons,

30:32.160 --> 30:41.120
that's Wolfowitz talking. The neoconservatives had infiltrated the White House. In April of 2002,

30:41.120 --> 30:44.800
a number of them would sign yet another letter, urging invasion,

30:44.800 --> 30:49.600
signed most prominently by now Defense Policy Advisory Committee Chairman Richard Pearl.

30:50.720 --> 30:55.520
Only the United States has the power and influence to provide meaningful assistance

30:55.520 --> 31:03.200
to our besieged ally. Mr. President, we urge you to accelerate plans for removing Saddam Hussein

31:03.200 --> 31:10.080
from power in Iraq. As you have said, every day that Saddam Hussein remains in power brings closer

31:10.080 --> 31:14.800
the day when terrorists will not just have airplanes with which to attack us, but chemical,

31:14.800 --> 31:21.920
biological, or nuclear weapons as well. It is now common knowledge that Saddam, along with Iran,

31:21.920 --> 31:28.560
is a funder and supporter of terrorism against Israel. Iraq has harbored terrorists such as Abu

31:28.560 --> 31:34.480
Nadal in the past, and it maintains links to the al-Qaeda network. If we do not move against

31:34.480 --> 31:41.040
Saddam Hussein and his regime, the damage our Israeli friends and we have suffered until now

31:41.040 --> 31:44.560
may someday appear but a prelude to much greater horrors.

31:46.400 --> 31:50.560
Now, I want to go back to Janine Zakaria's article for the Jerusalem Post,

31:50.560 --> 31:54.160
when she reported on the new appointees in the incoming Bush administration.

31:54.880 --> 31:59.120
There's one part that will surely stick out to some of you. It's about Bush's

31:59.120 --> 32:06.240
powerful Vice President Dick Cheney. Cheney is considered such a key player on foreign policy

32:06.240 --> 32:11.680
that people in Washington have started to refer to his staff as a shadow National Security Council.

32:12.320 --> 32:16.880
And while because of his business background, he is routinely referred to as an oil man by

32:16.880 --> 32:24.000
people in the pro-Israel community, a moniker which translate roughly as not sympathetic to Israel.

32:24.000 --> 32:29.840
I think you could make a case that on September 10th, 2001, it's not clear that George W. Bush was

32:30.400 --> 32:34.000
in any fundamental way going in our direction of foreign policy.

32:34.000 --> 32:37.920
That's Bill Kristol, co-founder of the Project for the New American Century,

32:37.920 --> 32:43.360
and son of Irving Kristol, mentioned earlier by Finkelstein as a founding father of neoconservatism.

32:43.360 --> 32:49.680
In fact, fellow neoconservative Jonah Goldberg described Kristol as the godfather of neoconservatism.

