I will work hard to find political solutions that allow and orderly and timely withdrawal

33:10.880 --> 33:17.840
from places like Kosovo and Bosnia. We will encourage our allies to take a broader role.

33:18.800 --> 33:25.920
We will not be hasty, but we will not be permanent peacekeepers dividing warring parties.

33:26.800 --> 33:31.120
And if you read Condi Rice's article in Foreign Affairs in 1999 to 2000,

33:31.840 --> 33:37.200
she was clearly the main adviser to Governor Bush. She was skeptical about a lot of these

33:37.760 --> 33:43.440
claims that the U.S. really had to shape a new world order that we had to engage in nation building.

33:43.440 --> 33:49.280
That article was Campaign 2000, Promoting the National Interest, published January 1st, 2000.

33:50.080 --> 33:55.200
From a section titled Coping with Rogue Regimes, Saddam Hussein's regime is isolated,

33:55.200 --> 34:00.000
his conventional military power has been severely weakened. The first line of defense should be

34:00.000 --> 34:06.320
a clear and classical statement of deterrence. If they do acquire WMD, their weapons will be

34:06.320 --> 34:10.880
unusable because any attempt to use them will bring national obliteration.

34:11.600 --> 34:16.640
We are able to keep arms from him. His military forces have not been rebuilt.

34:16.640 --> 34:21.280
