36:43.920 --> 36:48.240
and his obsession with Iraq, which perhaps planted the first seeds in convincing the

36:48.240 --> 36:54.240
administration to topple Saddam Hussein. But aside from Wolfowitz, another powerful figure

36:54.240 --> 37:00.320
was a critical mastermind that has escaped the same level of notoriety. His name is Irv Lewis

37:00.320 --> 37:05.600
Libby, known by his nickname Scooter. Max Frankel of the New York Times called him

37:05.600 --> 37:09.760
a poobah courtier who knew virtually all government secrets worth knowing.

37:11.040 --> 37:15.200
Bob Woodward explains his influence in his investigative account of the planning for

37:15.200 --> 37:20.080
the Iraq invasion. He was one of the most important players in the Bush National Security

37:20.080 --> 37:25.920
apparatus. Libby had three formal titles. He was Chief of Staff to Vice President Cheney,

37:25.920 --> 37:30.880
he was also National Security Advisor to the Vice President, and he was finally an assistant

37:30.880 --> 37:36.560
to President Bush. It was a trifecta of positions probably never held before by a single person.

37:37.760 --> 37:42.560
