missing WMD. There are indications that the US government souped up intelligence,

39:06.400 --> 39:12.320
leaned on spooks to change their conclusions, and concealed country information to deceive people

39:12.320 --> 39:18.400
at home and around the world. I'm told by a person involved in the Niger caper that more than a year

39:18.400 --> 39:23.680
ago, the Vice President's office asked for an investigation of the uranium deal. So a former

39:23.680 --> 39:29.920
US ambassador to Africa was dispatched to Niger. In February 2002, according to someone present

39:29.920 --> 39:34.640
at the meetings, that envoy reported to the CIA and State Department that the information was

39:34.640 --> 39:40.640
unequivocally wrong and that the document had been forged. This unnamed former US ambassador was a

39:40.640 --> 39:46.080
Joseph C. Wilson. He had been Ambo in Gabon and São Tomé, as well as head of African Affairs at

39:46.080 --> 39:50.880
Bill Clinton's National Security Council. As Max Frankel explains in The New York Times,

39:50.880 --> 39:56.800
Wilson's conclusions and other findings persuaded the CIA's director George Tenet to remove any

39:56.800 --> 40:02.720
mention of uranium sales from a presidential speech in October 2002, but the Niger scare

40:02.720 --> 40:08.000
resurfaced three months later, becoming a notorious 16 words. The British government

40:08.000 --> 40:13.600
has learned the Saddam Hussein recently sought significant quantities of uranium from Africa.

